WEBVTT

00:04.935 --> 00:07.598
<i>Previously on</i> The Truth About
the Harry Quebert Affair...

00:07.698 --> 00:08.759
Harry Quebert,

00:08.859 --> 00:10.601
allow me to present
Elijah Stern,

00:10.701 --> 00:11.842
who generously
funds this Gala.

00:11.942 --> 00:13.123
Oh.

00:13.223 --> 00:15.606
He also owns the house
you're renting at Goose Cove.

00:15.706 --> 00:17.488
Mr. Stern, a pleasure.

00:17.588 --> 00:19.570
I'd like to introduce you
to my right-hand man.

00:19.670 --> 00:21.492
Harry Quebert.

00:21.592 --> 00:22.673
[speech impediment]
Good evening, Mr. Quebert.

00:22.753 --> 00:24.615
My name is Luther Caleb.

00:24.715 --> 00:26.337
Look what I found
in his house.

00:26.437 --> 00:27.658
It's a nude painting.

00:27.758 --> 00:29.780
Look closer, Sherlock.

00:29.880 --> 00:32.303
Yeah, that's a naked painting
of Nola Kellergan

00:32.403 --> 00:34.665
in Elijah Stern's house, okay?

00:34.765 --> 00:36.227
Signed "LC."

00:36.327 --> 00:38.269
His chauffeur,
Luther Caleb.

00:38.369 --> 00:40.391
When I brought him up,
Stern went radio silent.

00:40.491 --> 00:41.712
I got Barnaski to back off.

00:41.812 --> 00:43.314
He's agreed to tear up
your contract.

00:43.414 --> 00:44.555
[Marcus]:
Yeah, in exchange for what?

00:44.655 --> 00:46.077
<i>All you have to do</i>

00:46.177 --> 00:48.559
<i>is write a book about</i>
<i>the Harry Quebert affair.</i>

00:48.659 --> 00:50.401
I lied to you

00:50.501 --> 00:51.603
when I told you that
I told my parents

00:51.703 --> 00:53.565
that I was staying
at Nancy's house.

00:53.665 --> 00:54.606
I didn't tell them anything.

00:54.706 --> 00:56.528
I just ran away.

00:56.628 --> 00:58.630
My mother told me
I had to be punished.

01:01.392 --> 01:02.554
[Marcus]: And so
what did you do with the paper?

01:02.634 --> 01:03.615
Did you tell anyone about it?

01:03.715 --> 01:04.656
[Tamara]: You bet I did.

01:04.756 --> 01:06.217
Chief Pratt.

01:06.317 --> 01:07.579
Don't worry.

01:07.679 --> 01:10.542
You'll see how we deal
with guys like that around here.

01:10.642 --> 01:12.644
Okay.

01:15.847 --> 01:17.108
<i>[Nancy]:</i>
<i>That's when she told me</i>

01:17.208 --> 01:18.630
<i>about her being in love</i>
<i>with an older man.</i>

01:18.730 --> 01:19.951
Didn't name names,

01:20.051 --> 01:21.753
but I was sure it was Stern.

01:21.853 --> 01:22.654
Did you ever
see them together?

01:22.734 --> 01:23.955
Nola and Stern?

01:24.055 --> 01:26.718
No. Like I told you,

01:26.818 --> 01:29.241
he'd just send that
deformed chauffeur of his.

01:29.341 --> 01:32.604
After she disappeared,
I told Chief Pratt everything.

01:32.704 --> 01:33.966
He promised he'd investigate.

01:34.066 --> 01:37.869
If I'd spoken up sooner,
she'd be alive today.

01:39.711 --> 01:42.914
